JOHANNESBURG - Charges of dagga possession against axe-murder accused, Henri van Breda were withdrawn on Tuesday.Van Breda was arrested with his girlfriend last year and the couple is currently out on bail.EXCLUSIVE: Stellenbosch murders - full emergency callThe 21-year-old also faces murder charges after he allegedly hacked his parents and brother to death in their Stellenbosch home in 2015. His sister survived the incident.Van Breda is out on R100,000 bail as the murder trial is expected to start on 24 April. eNCA